<br>
Ragefire, if camped in skyfire cannot be FCFS'd since verant has strict rules on first engagement. The new ragefire is kitable by anyone who can sow or run fast, heck maybe even jboots or runspeed3. <br>
<br>
SOOOO - with that in mind, a cleric and a tracking partner (druid, ranger, bard), who know about the spawn point of him (which has been pretty much confired he spawns in one spot then starts to roam), can immediately engage him upon his spawn and start kiting him until their raid forces arrive. Verant's policy is first engaged is first ones to have the opportunity to kill it. Those coming afterward and possibly stealing that mob from the kiter would be considered kill stealing.<br>
<br>
Look it up. I don't lie. So *IF* clerics choose to camp the Skyfire Ragefire, *AND* they engage it first by kiting, it is theirs. FCFS is out the door, and anyone KS'ing it can and WILL be proven and dealt with.<br>
<br>
